BundleParc-flow

You can provide either diffusion weighted imaging (DWI) volumes input, incl. related bvecs and bvals, or
fiber orientation distribution (FOD) volumes.

fODF **MUST** be in spherical harmonics (SH), `descoteaux07` basis of order 6 or 8, with stride of
-1,2,3,4. If you have any doubts, it is recommended that you use the --dwi input instead.

You can provide an input directory containing all FOD volumes using:
    --fodf=/path/to/[input]   Input directory containing your subjects
                    |
                    ├-- S1
                    |    ├-- *fodf.nii.gz
                    └-- S2
                         └-- *fodf.nii.gz

Or an input directory containing all DWI input using:
    --dwi=/path/to/[input]   Input directory containing your subjects
                    |
                    ├-- S1
                    |    ├-- *dwi.nii.gz
                    |    ├-- *dwi.bval
                    |    ├-- *dwi.bvec
                    └-- S2
                         ├-- *dwi.nii.gz
                         ├-- *dwi.bval
                         └-- *dwi.bvec

